import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["delay"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data["distance"])
    ax.axvline(data["distance"].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Distance: {:.2f}'.format(data["distance"].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by=['counts'], ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="counts", y="origin", hue="destination", data=data, dodge=False)
    ax.set(xlabel='Number of Flights', ylabel='Origin Airport')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y=data.index, data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
